and suitcases downstairs.

18:15.700 --> 18:18.340
And she didn't have any money
for the cab.

18:18.740 --> 18:20.540
And you paid for that?

18:20.580 --> 18:22.180
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

18:22.220 --> 18:24.260
- Hold my calls.
- Sure.

18:24.340 --> 18:26.060
I told you.

18:26.460 --> 18:28.460
When it's appropriate.

18:28.500 --> 18:30.380
You let me know.

18:31.660 --> 18:33.060
And could I have some water?

18:34.180 --> 18:36.060
Hello, gorgeous.

18:38.900 --> 18:40.500
What are you doing here?

18:40.540 --> 18:42.420
I'm sorry, Daddy.

18:43.500 --> 18:45.580
Please don't be angry with me.

18:45.620 --> 18:48.140
All right, I can guess what you've done,
but why don't you tell me,

18:48.180 --> 18:50.620
and then I'll decide.

18:51.300 --> 18:53.540
I dropped out of school.

18:56.140 --> 18:57.260
Oh, Jane.

18:57.300 --> 19:00.020
Okay, have you told your mother?

19:00.060 --> 19:01.980
No, I wanted to talk to you first.

19:02.020 --> 19:03.860
Well, you're going to have to tell her,
Jane, all right?

19:03.900 --> 19:05.540
I'm not going to do that for you.

19:06.500 --> 19:08.060
- Why can't you...
- Sit.

19:08.100 --> 19:11.980
And then, together,
the three of us will decide

19:12.020 --> 19:13.500
where to go from here.

19:13.540 --> 19:17.740
Okay, but I've thought a lot about this.
College is a waste of time for me.

19:18.380 --> 19:19.780
How does...

19:20.020 --> 19:23.300
How does somebody know that halfway
through their freshman year?

19:23.340 --> 19:26.100
You didn't even go to college, Daddy,
and you're successful.

19:26.140 --> 19:28.500
I want to come work for you.

19:30.500 --> 19:34.180
She's not telling you everything.
She's hiding something.

19:34.460 --> 19:35.900
I know.

19:39.660 --> 19:41.100
I'm not hiring right now, sweetheart.

19:41.140 --> 19:42.860
Okay, but just listen to me for one second.

19:42.900 --> 19:44.180
Jane.

19:44.220 --> 19:45.380
All right.

19:45.420 --> 19:47.220
Look, what would happen to the business,

19:47.260 --> 19:50.540
if, God forbid,
something were to happen to you?

19:50.980 --> 19:52.020
Okay.

19:52.060 --> 19:55.140
Mom would probably have to
sell to strangers.

19:55.180 --> 19:57.100
Now, look,
I'm willing to start at the bottom.

19:57.140 --> 19:59.780
You can treat me like a regular employee.

19:59.820 --> 20:04.100
I just want to learn everything there is
to know about running the box business.

20:04.140 --> 20:06.500
Then, when the time comes,

20:07.180 --> 20:09.460
it can stay in the family.

20:09.700 --> 20:10.940
Hmm.

20:12.260 --> 20:14.420
Well, that's sweet, honey, but

20:14.460 --> 20:17.220
