But one sudden move

01:37:11.320 --> 01:37:16.360
and I drop you, and I make sure
that your family knows what you are.

01:37:19.680 --> 01:37:21.440
I understand.

01:37:31.720 --> 01:37:34.760
You've come down in the world,
Mr. Baffert.

01:37:46.280 --> 01:37:49.360
Take your hand
out of your pocket real slow.

01:37:52.600 --> 01:37:54.480
You don't want to climb over, do you?

01:37:54.520 --> 01:37:57.560
What are you doing
with the key to a cemetery?

01:37:57.600 --> 01:37:59.120
I own it.

01:38:00.480 --> 01:38:02.000
Why do you own a cemetery?

01:38:02.040 --> 01:38:05.120
Well, you always want to invest in things
that people can't do without.

01:38:05.160 --> 01:38:08.400
Water and cemeteries? Pretty safe bets.

01:38:13.200 --> 01:38:16.960
Here, you'll need this to get out.

01:39:45.000 --> 01:39:46.520
Fuck!

01:39:49.960 --> 01:39:51.280
Fuck!

01:39:56.240 --> 01:39:57.880
Hey, Atwood!

01:39:59.000 --> 01:40:01.240
I want to show you something.

01:40:24.200 --> 01:40:25.440
Okay.

01:40:26.960 --> 01:40:28.720
There we are.

01:40:33.880 --> 01:40:35.320
Okay.

01:40:35.440 --> 01:40:41.240
Now, if I stand here and you stand there...
Not...

01:40:41.280 --> 01:40:45.920
Not too far away, and you shoot me,
I should...

01:40:46.760 --> 01:40:50.040
I should fall straight back into this hole.

01:40:52.720 --> 01:40:56.080
You don't think I have the guts to do this,
do you?

01:40:56.120 --> 01:41:00.280
No, I'm hoping you do, Mr. Smith.
I'm hoping you do.

01:41:02.000 --> 01:41:04.080
Okay, let's...

01:41:05.920 --> 01:41:08.160
Let's get this over with.

01:41:19.520 --> 01:41:21.600
I'll close my eyes.

01:41:45.560 --> 01:41:47.680
I'm sorry, Mr. Smith.

01:41:50.800 --> 01:41:53.480
I really did want you to kill me.

01:41:54.200 --> 01:41:58.840
But in case at the last minute
I changed my mind,

01:41:58.880 --> 01:42:04.520
I returned to your apartment
and I bent the firing pin on your gun.

01:42:06.800 --> 01:42:11.440
In fact, I even brought another one
for you to use so you could finish me,

01:42:11.480 --> 01:42:14.520
if I had decided to go through with it.

01:42:15.720 --> 01:42:19.520
Unfortunately for you,
my daughter's pregnant.

01:42:19.560 --> 01:42:22.080
And just before you pulled that trigger,

01:42:22.120 --> 01:42:26.280
I realized how much
I want to see the end of that story.

01:42:26.960 --> 01:42:28.280
Don't do this to me.

01:42:28.320 --> 01:42:31.520
If you touch even a hair on my head,
the cops are going to find those pictures.

01:42:31.560 --> 01:42:34.560
And they're going to know
that you killed that couple.

01:42:34.600 --> 01:42:38.240
The contents of your safety deposit box,
Mr. Smith,

01:42:40.600 --> 01:42:42.320
have vanished.

01:42:46.400 --> 01:42:48.440
It hurts, doesn't it?

01:42:48.880 --> 01:42:51.120
Help me!

01:43:14.400 --> 01:43:18.840
Before I was the Thumbprint Killer,
Mr. Smith,

01:43:18.880 --> 01:43:23.480
I killed a lot of people
in a lot of different ways.

01:43:50.120 --> 01:43:51.520
Thank you.

01:44:05.080 --> 01:44:08.400
It says there
that the Thumbprint Killer is a monster.

01:44:09.720 --> 01:44:13.240
Annoys you a little bit
you can't take credit, doesn't it?

01:44:13.280 --> 01:44:18.160
No. Anyone who's good
at what they do wants credit,

01:44:18.200 --> 01:44:24.960
but since I'm not going to do it anymore,
I will let Mr. Smith have the credit.

01:44:26.360 --> 01:44:29.120
Don't kid yourself, Earl.
You're going to kill again.

01:44:29.160 --> 01:44:31.200
No, I'm not.

01:44:31.600 --> 01:44:35.720
I'm going back to the AA meetings,
and I will control it.

01:44:44.920 --> 01:44:47.680
But there is an answer
I would like to have.

01:44:52.160 --> 01:44:55.040
- Atwood.
- Why are you a cop?

01:44:55.080 --> 01:44:56.520
Who is this?

01:44:56.880 --> 01:44:59.520
You're rich. You have a good education.

01:44:59.560 --> 01:45:01.200
You could have gone
into your father's business.

01:45:01.240 --> 01:45:05.480
Instead you went outside all of that
and became successful on your own. Why?

01:45:05.600 --> 01:45:07.040
If you want something from me,

01:45:07.080 --> 01:45:09.920
then you're going to have to tell me
who you are or I'm going to hang up.

01:45:10.240 --> 01:45:12.840
Did you think your husband's killing
was random?

01:45:13.520 --> 01:45:16.320
And I certainly didn't have to
give you Meeks,

01:45:16.360 --> 01:45:18.120
Mr. Baffert?

01:45:18.600 --> 01:45:22.400
- What's the answer?
- You don't sound like you.

01:45:23.680 --> 01:45:25.720
Well, I have a little cold.

01:45:25.840 --> 01:45:29.480
- Are you going to give me the answer?
- Where are you?

01:45:29.760 --> 01:45:33.960
I'll tell you, if you can give me
the true answer to my question.

01:45:45.040 --> 01:45:50.320
My father was very disappointed that
I was born a girl and he let me know it.

01:45:51.840 --> 01:45:54.880
I've spent my whole life
trying to prove him wrong.

01:45:56.720 --> 01:45:58.160
Thank you.

01:45:58.480 --> 01:46:01.800
Wait!
You promised to tell me where you are.

01:46:01.920 --> 01:46:03.160
Me?

01:46:04.920 --> 01:46:07.160
I'm on top of a building.

01:46:12.800 --> 01:46:14.800
That wasn't Baffert.

01:48:02.080 --> 01:48:03.680
Oh, Jane.

01:48:04.680 --> 01:48:05.920
Jane.

01:48:40.360 --> 01:48:41.800
Jane!

01:48:43.440 --> 01:48:44.400
Jane!

01:48:44.440 --> 01:48:45.800
Earl, honey, wake up.

01:48:45.840 --> 01:48:47.200
Wake up.

01:48:48.960 --> 01:48:50.200
You were dreaming.

01:48:51.600 --> 01:48:56.160
Oh, Emma. I was... I woke you up.

01:48:56.440 --> 01:48:59.560
It's okay. It's okay.

01:49:01.120 --> 01:49:04.400
- Oh, God.
- I'm here. Go back to sleep.

01:49:09.640 --> 01:49:12.680
Why do you fight it so hard,
Earl?

01:49:12.720 --> 01:49:17.040
God, grant me the serenity
to accept the things I cannot change,

01:49:17.080 --> 01:49:21.360
courage to change the things I can,
and wisdom to know the difference.

01:49:21.800 --> 01:49:24.120
Living one day at a time
and enjoying one moment at a time,

01:49:24.160 --> 01:49:26.360
accepting hardships
as the pathway to peace.

01:49:26.400 --> 01:49:30.480
Taking, as He did, this sinful world
as it is and not as I would have it,

01:49:30.520 --> 01:49:33.720
trusting that He will make all things
right if I surrender to His will,

01:49:33.760 --> 01:49:36.240
that I may be reasonably happy in this life,

01:49:36.280 --> 01:49:40.600
and supremely happy with Him
forever in the next. Amen.

